WEBVTT

00:58.100 --> 00:59.477
SHAGGY:
That's my pal.

00:59.894 --> 01:02.021
Scooby-Dooby-Doo!

01:13.908 --> 01:16.702
[THUNDER CRACKING]

01:31.092 --> 01:32.718
Weather Eye One to base...

01:32.885 --> 01:35.680
...we're about to enter the hurricane eye
any second.

01:35.846 --> 01:38.975
Position, center of Bermuda Triangle.

01:39.141 --> 01:43.396
It's weird how quiet it is
in the eye of a hurricane.

01:43.562 --> 01:45.398
Look!

01:46.315 --> 01:49.485
Dead ahead. What is that?

01:50.069 --> 01:53.406
| don't know. Pilot to base.
This is incredible.

01:53.572 --> 01:58.160
A huge unidentified flying object
coming straight at us, it's--

01:59.954 --> 02:02.373
MAN:
Weather Eye One, continue message.

02:02.540 --> 02:06.043
Weather Eye One, come in.
Weather Eye One.

02:08.378 --> 02:10.089
We've lost all contact.

02:10.256 --> 02:12.133
Dr. Grimsley, what happened?

02:12.300 --> 02:15.011
GRIMSLEY: I'm only a weather scientist,
Captain Harris.

02:15.177 --> 02:17.179
-What do you think?
-| don't know.

02:17.346 --> 02:21.726
But with your permission, sir,
I'd like to fly out there and find out.

02:21.892 --> 02:23.602
[UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO]

02:23.769 --> 02:28.274
VELMA: This is the life. Sailing on the
warm waters of the Gulf Stream.

02:28.441 --> 02:31.110
With plenty of good music.

02:32.278 --> 02:36.657
And, like, a teensy-weensy snack
to fight off sea sickness. Ha, ha, ha.

02:36.866 --> 02:39.327
[HUMMING]

02:41.078 --> 02:42.455
Huh?

02:52.798 --> 02:54.342
[LAUGHS]

02:57.970 --> 02:59.055
Huh?

02:59.263 --> 03:01.307
Isn't that delicious?

03:04.018 --> 03:06.437
Oh, boy, oh, boy, oh, boy.

03:06.645 --> 03:11.067
Like | always say,
"First come, first serve."

03:12.777 --> 03:14.945
Zoinks! Where'd it go?

03:18.783 --> 03:20.826
Huh? Where'd it go?

03:20.993 --> 03:22.953
Cool it, you two.

03:23.996 --> 03:28.667
-The wind's starting to blow pretty hard.
DAPHNE: Wow. look at those dark clouds.

03:28.834 --> 03:31.003
VELMA:
A big storm's coming this way.

03:31.170 --> 03:33.172
Right, Velma. We'd better head in.

03:33.339 --> 03:37.009
MAN [ON RADIO]: We interrupt this
program for a news bulletin in from Miami.

03:37.176 --> 03:40.805
A hurricane hunter plane has
disappeared in the Bermuda Triangle.

03:41.680 --> 03:43.474
-Disappeared?
-Yeah, Scoob.

03:43.641 --> 03:47.686
Ships and plane have been disappearing
in the Bermuda Triangle for years.

03:47.853 --> 03:49.021
Ships and planes?

03:49.188 --> 03:52.525
And the storm is blowing us
right into it.

03:52.691 --> 03:54.985
Hang on, it's getting worse.

03:57.988 --> 04:00.783
-We're ready for anything.
-We are?

04:02.785 --> 04:05.454
DAPHNE:
Look out. A monster wave.

04:05.663 --> 04:07.289
[SCOOBY SCREAMING]

04:20.344 --> 04:23.848
Quit clowning, you two.
Get the mainsail down.

04:24.014 --> 04:25.766
Okay.

04:31.647 --> 04:33.315
Help!

04:33.774 --> 04:35.234
[THUNDER CRACKS]

04:35.860 --> 04:37.194
[SHAGGY SCREAMING]

04:37.361 --> 04:40.072
We've lost our mast.
Like, we are doomed.

04:44.869 --> 04:46.704
We're goners, we're fi--

04:46.871 --> 04:48.539
Hey.

04:50.207 --> 04:52.877
-Where did the storm go?
-Yeah.

04:53.043 --> 04:56.046
VELMA: We've drifted into
the hurricane eye where it's calm.

04:56.213 --> 04:57.715
But we're still in trouble.

04:57.882 --> 04:59.967
We could drift like this for days.

05:00.134 --> 05:01.510
[AIRPLANE APPROACHING]

05:02.303 --> 05:05.890
Like, we're saved.
It's a plane. It's a plane.

05:06.056 --> 05:07.099
DAPHNE:
| see it.

05:07.266 --> 05:10.227
SHAGGY & SCOOBY:
Help! Help!

05:10.394 --> 05:13.189
Look down here.

05:16.358 --> 05:19.278
It's no use, Scooby. They don't see us.

05:19.445 --> 05:21.197
We're too far off.

05:21.363 --> 05:23.157
Hey, what's that?

05:25.034 --> 05:26.243
[GULPS]

05:26.410 --> 05:28.204
It's a flying saucer.

05:28.370 --> 05:30.164
Flying saucer?

05:30.748 --> 05:33.292
VELMA:
It's heading for the plane.

05:34.335 --> 05:36.962
DAPHNE:
Jeepers, did you see that?

05:37.129 --> 05:39.965
I'll bet that's what happened
to the weather plane.

05:40.132 --> 05:42.968
Any maybe that's what's
gonna happen to us.

05:43.135 --> 05:45.804
-Let's get moving.
-Yeah, moving.

05:45.971 --> 05:47.348
Without a mast?

05:47.515 --> 05:50.392
Like we gotta do something, Scoob.

05:58.651 --> 06:01.779
DAPHNE:
Oh, no, we're back in the storm again.

06:04.240 --> 06:06.242
FRED:
Look, there's an island ahead.

06:06.408 --> 06:10.120
SHAGGY: Yeah, but like we're gonna--
We're gonna hit that big rock.

06:11.247 --> 06:13.207
[SHAGGY SCREAMING]

06:13.958 --> 06:16.168
Oh, boy, that was close.

06:22.341 --> 06:23.759
[GASPS]

06:30.057 --> 06:31.267
Phew.

06:31.433 --> 06:34.019
DAPHNE:
Oh, thank heavens, we're safe.

06:34.186 --> 06:37.731
You call this safe? She call this safe.
Ha, ha, ha.

06:37.898 --> 06:41.735
Shipwrecked on an island
in the Bermuda Triangle. Ha, ha, ha.

06:45.197 --> 06:48.701
FRED: According to this map
it's called Diablo Island.

06:49.702 --> 06:52.454
And you can relax, Shaggy.
It's deserted.

06:52.621 --> 06:54.832
VELMA:
So there's nobody around but us.

07:10.723 --> 07:13.559
DAPHNE:
It sure gets cold on this island.

07:13.726 --> 07:15.769
FRED:
Yeah, we need more firewood.

07:15.936 --> 07:18.606
Shaggy, Scooby,
see what you can scare up.

07:18.772 --> 07:20.566
Did you have to say "scare up"?

07:20.733 --> 07:22.484
We are plenty scared all ready.

07:22.651 --> 07:26.113
Come on, fellas,
do it for a Scooby snack.

07:26.280 --> 07:29.283
BOTH:
Like, no way. Uh-uh.

07:29.950 --> 07:33.245
How about two Scooby snacks.

07:34.580 --> 07:39.293
-Oh, okay. Three Scooby snacks?
BOTH: Uh-huh, uh-huh, uh-huh.

07:44.715 --> 07:47.635
-Come on, Scoob, lets go.
-Okay.

07:48.677 --> 07:50.220
[SNIFFING]

07:59.438 --> 08:00.564
[SCOOBY GULPS]

08:00.731 --> 08:05.486
-Get off this island.
-Ah!

08:06.528 --> 08:10.407
[SCOOBY RAMBLING INDISTINCTLY]

08:10.574 --> 08:12.117
DAPHNE:
What's wrong, Scoob?

08:12.284 --> 08:16.664
SHAGGY: An old man.
Only one eye. And the beard.

08:16.830 --> 08:18.832
SCOOBY:
Yeah. Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

08:19.667 --> 08:21.335
What did he say, Scoob.

08:21.502 --> 08:25.589
"Get off this island."

08:28.342 --> 08:30.052
[SHAGGY & SCOOBY SCREAMING]

08:32.136 --> 08:37.684
MAN: Get off or the skeleton men
will get you.

08:37.934 --> 08:40.479
SHAGGY:
Skeleton men?

08:41.230 --> 08:44.107
MAN:
This island is haunted.

08:44.274 --> 08:45.693
It's haunted?

08:45.859 --> 08:48.487
SHAGGY:
| knew it. | knew it.

08:49.697 --> 08:51.615
Get your boat and go...

08:51.782 --> 08:54.368
...while you still can.

08:54.535 --> 08:57.913
DAPHNE: He disappeared.
-Like, you heard what the man said.

08:58.080 --> 09:00.624
Let's get out off this island
while we can.

09:00.791 --> 09:01.834
SCOOBY:
Yeah.

09:02.000 --> 09:04.169
VELMA:
Hold it, you too.

09:05.337 --> 09:06.630
We're not leaving.

09:06.797 --> 09:08.132
FRED:
Velma is right.

09:08.298 --> 09:11.468
Because we could be right on the verge
of solving a great mystery.

09:11.635 --> 09:14.096
The riddle of the Bermuda Triangle.

09:14.304 --> 09:19.309
Zoinks! Heh, heh. Between skeleton man
and flying saucers, I'd rather not know.

09:19.476 --> 09:22.312
VELMA: We'll start by searching
the island for clues.

09:22.479 --> 09:26.775
-Up there? In the dark?
-Uh-uh.

09:26.942 --> 09:30.821
Look, like, we'll stay here
and keep the fire going. Okay?

09:30.988 --> 09:33.490
FRED: That's a good idea.
-It is?

09:33.657 --> 09:36.118
Yeah, it'll help us find our way back.

09:36.285 --> 09:37.327
Let's go.

09:38.036 --> 09:39.413
[VELMA PANTING]

09:39.580 --> 09:46.211
Next time, we'll go sailing I'll remember
to bring my mountain-climbing shoes.

09:46.378 --> 09:50.841
Hey, look, it levels off,
like some kind of field.

09:51.008 --> 09:54.678
FRED: It looks like a abandoned airstrip
probably used in World War I1...

09:54.845 --> 09:56.680
...for sub-patrol planes.

09:56.847 --> 10:00.434
VELMA: Good guess.
There's the old airstrip control tower...

10:00.601 --> 10:02.478
...practically falling apart.

10:03.020 --> 10:04.104
[THUMP]

10:04.271 --> 10:06.148
DAPHNE: Hey!
-What happened?

10:06.315 --> 10:08.692
| tripped over something.

10:08.859 --> 10:12.905
FRED: Looks like a smudge pot. And it
hasn't been too long since it was lighted.

10:13.071 --> 10:15.741
VELMA:
Look, two long rows of them.

10:15.908 --> 10:17.534
FRED:
And wheel drags.

10:17.701 --> 10:21.997
Jeepers, maybe this is where
the flying saucer lands.

10:22.164 --> 10:25.292
But why would a UFO
needs old-fashioned smudge pots...

10:25.459 --> 10:27.252
...to light up a landing strip.

10:27.419 --> 10:31.256
Good question.
Let's check out the control tower.

10:32.341 --> 10:34.176
FRED:
This is all modern equipment.

10:34.343 --> 10:36.094
Direction finders, radar.

10:36.261 --> 10:39.389
Everything you need to guide
a plane down on instruments.

10:39.556 --> 10:42.017
VELMA: But why would any plane
want to land here...

10:42.184 --> 10:43.936
...in the middle of nowhere.

10:44.102 --> 10:49.233
Hey, look. Those wheel tracks run
right up to the side of the mountain.

10:49.566 --> 10:53.278
FRED: Hm. We better check this out.
Let's follow those tracks.

10:53.779 --> 10:55.864
Are you get any clams, Scoob?

10:56.031 --> 10:57.074
SCOOBY:
Yeah.

10:57.241 --> 10:59.952
One for Shaggy, two for me.

11:00.118 --> 11:03.497
One for Shaggy, two for me.

11:10.295 --> 11:11.922
[SCOOBY WHIMPERING]

11:14.758 --> 11:16.552
Boy, oh, boy. Ha, ha.

11:16.718 --> 11:18.846
We're gonna have clam chowder.

11:19.012 --> 11:20.973
[SCOOBY'S TEETH CHATTERING]

11:21.139 --> 11:22.766
Clam up, Scoob.

11:22.933 --> 11:24.852
[SCOOBY WHIMPERING]

11:26.937 --> 11:29.523
SHAGGY & SCOOBY:
Skeleton men!

11:29.690 --> 11:31.859
[SKELETON MEN GROWLING]

11:35.404 --> 11:37.281
[SHAGGY & SCOOBY'S
TEETH CHATTERING]

11:37.447 --> 11:39.032
BOTH:
Yikes!

11:45.038 --> 11:47.499
-Like, let's hide in this old ventilator.
-Okay.

11:48.917 --> 11:52.004
-Help, Shaggy!
-Zoinks!

11:56.091 --> 11:57.968
[BOTH SCREAMING]

11:59.803 --> 12:01.722
[SPLASH]

12:09.646 --> 12:11.064
[SPLASH]

12:15.319 --> 12:17.779
Like, where are we?

12:17.946 --> 12:19.823
| don't know.

12:20.324 --> 12:22.659
The wheel marks go right to the cliff.

12:22.826 --> 12:25.829
This rusty wheel might be the answer.

12:26.246 --> 12:28.040
[SQUEAKING]

12:30.751 --> 12:33.879
Jeepers, the cliff's sliding open.

12:35.756 --> 12:37.549
Except it isn't a cliff.

12:37.716 --> 12:41.261
It's plaster covering huge doors.

12:41.428 --> 12:43.847
Let's see what's inside.

12:46.224 --> 12:51.271
VELMA: Jinkies, look, the weather planes
that were swallowed by the flying saucer.

12:51.438 --> 12:54.608
But what are they doing here
inside a mountain?

12:54.775 --> 12:59.738
When we find out, we'll be closer to
solving this mystery. Come on.

12:59.905 --> 13:02.074
Like, wow, Scooby, look at that.

13:06.578 --> 13:08.705
SCOOBY:
Submarine?

13:12.334 --> 13:15.379
And a dock, Scoob. Come on.

13:47.828 --> 13:49.705
[CLANKING]

13:49.871 --> 13:52.416
Like, stop moving, Scooby.

13:52.582 --> 13:54.042
I'm not.

13:54.209 --> 13:55.293
[CLANKING]

13:55.460 --> 13:56.753
[BOTH SCREAM]

13:56.920 --> 13:59.464
-Help!
-Help!

13:59.631 --> 14:02.801
SHAGGY:
This way, Scoob, into the raft.

14:02.968 --> 14:05.220
[SKELETON MEN GROWLING]

14:06.888 --> 14:09.307
SHAGGY:
Here they come. Start the engine.

14:09.474 --> 14:12.269
I'm trying. I'm trying.

14:12.602 --> 14:14.438
[ENGINE SPUTTERING]

14:15.272 --> 14:17.441
[WHIMPERING]

14:18.483 --> 14:22.279
Come on, Scoob, stop fooling around.
Those guys are almost here.

14:32.456 --> 14:37.252
Zoinks! Like, we forgot to cast off
the mooring lines.

14:40.547 --> 14:43.592
SHAGGY: Help!
SCOOBY: Help!

14:49.431 --> 14:50.599
Zoinks!

14:50.766 --> 14:53.060
Look out, Scoob.

14:54.436 --> 14:58.356
Hang on, Scooby.

15:01.526 --> 15:02.903
[SCOOBY GASPS]

15:05.322 --> 15:06.448
[THUMP]

15:08.241 --> 15:09.951
VELMA:
See anything unusual?

15:10.118 --> 15:11.870
Nope, not a clue.

15:12.037 --> 15:14.372
| wonder if the radio still works.

15:14.539 --> 15:15.749
Good thinking, Daphne.

15:16.374 --> 15:18.960
This is, Weather Eye One
calling weather base.

15:19.127 --> 15:22.339
FRED: Come in, please.
Weather Eye One calling base.

15:22.506 --> 15:24.174
Weather Eye One?

15:24.341 --> 15:26.218
Yes, sir, with good news.

15:26.384 --> 15:28.720
-Your planes didn't crash.
-What?

15:28.887 --> 15:32.849
They are here on Diablo Islands inside
an underground hangar.

15:33.016 --> 15:37.104
I'll notify the authorities.
Stay put until we get there.

15:37.521 --> 15:41.691
That's funny. It looks like somebody's
repainting the plane.

15:41.858 --> 15:44.694
Now this mystery
is starting to make sense.

15:44.861 --> 15:47.114
Come on, let's keep looking for clues.

15:48.406 --> 15:50.659
VELMA:
Let's look in here.

15:53.161 --> 15:54.788
A dead end.

15:54.955 --> 15:56.456
It's filling up with water.

16:03.004 --> 16:05.632
Oh, gosh, we're trapped.

16:06.424 --> 16:08.885
Like, how lucky can we get, Scoob.

16:09.052 --> 16:12.931
We'll be safe from the skeleton men
in this sub.

16:17.060 --> 16:18.436
[SQUAWKS]

16:21.565 --> 16:22.649
[GASPS]

16:22.816 --> 16:25.277
Zoinks, like, what's wrong, Scoob?

16:27.237 --> 16:31.074
Relax, Scoob. Ha, ha, ha.
It's only a little bird.

16:31.241 --> 16:32.868
A little bird?

16:33.076 --> 16:34.828
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

16:38.206 --> 16:40.917
Little bird? Heh, heh, heh.

16:41.793 --> 16:44.546
Ah! The skeleton men!

16:44.713 --> 16:48.800
Zoinks, they're here.
We gotta hide. Come on.

16:50.635 --> 16:52.721
SCOOBY: What's that?
-Like, that's crazy.

16:52.888 --> 16:54.848
A submarine with a skylight.

16:55.223 --> 16:57.142
[SHAGGY SCREAMING]

17:01.980 --> 17:05.608
-Like, quick hide in there.
-Okay.

17:05.983 --> 17:07.986
[SKELETON MEN GROWLING]

17:08.444 --> 17:09.738
Zoinks!

17:09.945 --> 17:12.031
[SKELETON MEN GROWLING]

17:15.242 --> 17:20.040
SCOOBY:
Help! Help! Help!

17:23.501 --> 17:26.838
Help! Help!

17:27.005 --> 17:28.673
Help, help!

17:28.840 --> 17:33.220
Jeepers, we're doomed.

17:35.055 --> 17:36.890
VELMA:
Somebody dropped us a rope.

17:37.057 --> 17:39.601
FRED:
Quick, let's go.

17:41.186 --> 17:45.148
DAPHNE: But there's no one here.
-Well, the door didn't open by itself.

17:45.315 --> 17:48.235
And what about the ladder?
Somebody saved us.

17:48.401 --> 17:50.820
And | think | know who did.

17:50.987 --> 17:55.367
Look, a submarine.
Come on, let's investigate.

17:59.788 --> 18:01.539
SHAGGY:
Excuse me.

18:02.040 --> 18:04.125
Like, who are you guys?

18:04.292 --> 18:05.710
[MAN MUMBLING]

18:05.919 --> 18:08.546
SHAGGY:
Come on, speak up. | can't hear you.

18:08.713 --> 18:10.548
[MAN MUMBLING]

18:10.715 --> 18:12.342
[SKELETON MEN GROWLING]

18:12.509 --> 18:16.263
Yikes, | gotta go.
Nice talking to you.

18:19.391 --> 18:20.684
Zoinks! Ha, ha.

18:20.850 --> 18:23.228
Like, what happened?

18:23.436 --> 18:25.230
[LASER HUMMING]

18:25.855 --> 18:28.733
-What's that weird sound?
-Look.

18:29.901 --> 18:32.612
FRED:
The flying saucer.

18:33.113 --> 18:37.242
VELMA: And now it's gone.
-Jeepers, what's that?

18:41.955 --> 18:44.624
-It's Scooby.
-But where's Shaggy?

18:44.791 --> 18:46.918
There he is.

18:47.877 --> 18:49.504
[GROWLING]

18:51.214 --> 18:52.340
[SPLASH]

18:52.507 --> 18:57.721
SHAGGY:
Help, help! Somebody save me!

18:57.887 --> 19:00.890
SCOOBY:
I'll save you, Shaggy.

19:03.935 --> 19:08.315
Hey, Scoob. Over here.
Give me a hand.

19:10.442 --> 19:15.155
Phew. Like, thanks, Scoob.
Those skeletons almost got me.

19:20.368 --> 19:21.536
I've got an idea.

19:21.703 --> 19:25.457
Like, faster, Scooby, faster.
Those guys are getting on us.

19:25.623 --> 19:28.626
Do something, Scooby.

19:30.462 --> 19:34.841
Hey, Shaggy, Scooby. This way.

19:43.058 --> 19:48.355
-Not bad. Three fish with one hook.
-Over here, Fred.

19:48.772 --> 19:51.900
Yay! We got them.

19:52.067 --> 19:55.653
Quick, the captured men are tied up
in the sub. Like, we gotta get them.

19:55.820 --> 19:56.863
-Come on, Scoob.
-Okay.

19:59.282 --> 20:01.117
[BOTH GASP]

20:01.284 --> 20:03.370
BOTH:
The old seadog!

20:03.578 --> 20:06.873
Help!

20:07.040 --> 20:09.751
Well, you chickens
can stop running now.

20:09.918 --> 20:12.879
Are you kidding?
That old seadog is after us.

20:13.046 --> 20:14.297
We gotta hide.

20:14.464 --> 20:16.758
The old seadog's on our side.

20:16.925 --> 20:19.928
-Like, huh?
-On our side?

20:20.095 --> 20:23.098
You're very smart, miss.
I'm Commander Stern...

20:23.264 --> 20:25.183
...United States Navy Intelligence.

20:25.350 --> 20:29.270
-Navy Intelligence?
-We figured you were the one...

20:29.437 --> 20:32.065
...who saved us from that
flooding dry dock, commander.

20:32.232 --> 20:33.274
Thanks.

20:33.441 --> 20:37.028
And the Navy thanks all of you
for solving this mystery.

20:37.195 --> 20:38.488
Hey, your welcome.

20:38.655 --> 20:40.657
But do you mind
running through it once...

20:40.824 --> 20:43.243
...S0 Scooby and |
understand what was going on.

20:43.410 --> 20:47.831
FRED: It was all a plot to take advantage of
the mysterious Bermuda Triangle legend...

20:47.997 --> 20:50.375
...about disappearing
ships and plains.

20:50.542 --> 20:52.168
VELMA:
The saucer was a fake.

20:52.335 --> 20:56.005
A holographic image projected
onto the clouds by the submarine...

20:56.172 --> 20:59.092
...to make everyone think that planes
were being swallowed...

20:59.259 --> 21:01.678
...by an unidentified flying object.

21:03.346 --> 21:07.183
DAPHNE: Then the planes were flown
on remote control to the island airstrip.

21:07.350 --> 21:10.687
VELMA: Where the thieves were
